                            <comment id="27764" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2007 03:13:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;getBeansOfType&apos;s allowEagerInit flag only refers to eager initialization &lt;b&gt;for type matching purposes&lt;/b&gt;: So Spring won&apos;t instantiate such beans just for finding out whether the type matches. However, if the type does match, then the bean is instantiated and returned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With respect to the general ApplicationListener handling, please refer to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-4054&quot; title=&quot;ApplicationListener beans eagerly instantiated even when marked as lazy-init&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-4054&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-4054&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which raised the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
